# Ironwater — the dyad voice: two-note harmony needs NO width and NO mud.
# Triangle core with a quiet sine octave, high key-tracking so upper
# dyads stay glassy, hpf at 130 so nothing fights the bass, modest fixed
# cutoff, near-zero resonance. Fast enough to speak on the 3.5-beat
# anticipations, short release so changes stay legible.
